                    "company": "Radboudumc",
                    "description": "Project: Quantification of ASL and DTI Data in the Brain of Patients with Alzheimer\u2019s Disease.\n\nI did my graduation internship in the department of geriatrics of the RadboudUMC. For research done in the apartment, I was asked to develop a method to quantify ASL and DTI values and develop an automated processing pipeline. This was done in Matlab by using the FMRIB's Software Library. The next step was testing this pipeline and using it on a database of brainscans of patients. Another part of this internship was verifying and calibrating the ASL method. The pipeline I created was used as a basis for further development of the method and the rest of the study. \n\nNext to my research, I worked as a clinical intern in the department of geriatrics and assisted with patient tests. This included interviewing patients in the policlinic and basic patient care.",
