                    "description": "Project: An Automated MRI Pipeline for Connectivity Analysis in Infants at High Familial Risk for Autism: Adapting CIVET.\n\nMy last Master 2 internship was at the ACElab in the Montreal Neurological Institute of the McGill University. Here I worked to adapt the CIVET automated processing pipeline for use in infants under 2 years of age. Adapting the pipeline meant converting and adjusting tissue masks, threshold values and similar variables. It also meant that I had to do a lot of quality control and testing of the pipeline. This meant I had to learn how the pipeline worked in a relatively short time. During this internship, I expanded my knowledge of various programming languages and learned more about neuroimaging and processing pipelines.",
