                    "company": "Amsterdam UMC",
                    "description": "Project: Fluid Velocity Calculations with the Radon Transformation in Mouse Cerebral Vessels.\n\nFor one of my master internships, I worked in the department of biomedical engineering and physics of the Academic Medical Center in Amsterdam. I was asked to create a program that could be used to measure the velocity of blood in the brains of mice. By using a high-speed camera, we could track the movement of the red blood cells in the vessels. By creating line scan images, we could use a radon transform to calculate the velocity of blood in the vessels. I then created a graphical user interface in matlab for easier use of this method. This program was used for further study of blood velocity in the brain vessels of mice and the effects of neurovascular coupling.",
