                    "description": "Project: An In-Vitro Analysis of Osteogenic Differentiation of Mesenchymal Stem Cells after Clavicular Fracture: A Pilot Study.\n\nFor my second internship, I worked in the department of Traumatology of the University Medical Centre Utrecht. To evaluate if mesenchymal stem cells could be used to quicken the recovery process of clavicular fractures, I was asked to study the growth of mesenchymal stem cells and see if they could differentate into osteoblasts and osteocytes. I used tissue acquired during clavicular repair surgery to study the cells. The samples were cultured in our lab and the cells were dyed and fixated after a different number of days. The number of cells could then be measured by a fluorescence reader. During my internship, I learned how to work in a sterile lab and learned to culture stem cells.",
